<p>French President Emmanuel Macron announced on Sunday that Camilo Castro, a French-Chilean national detained in Venezuela since late June, has been released and returned to French authorities. Castro disappeared at the Paraguachon border crossing on June 26 while attempting to renew an expired Colombian residency visa, his family has said. French officials described the outcome as the result of diplomatic efforts to secure his freedom.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/-6Fzo0KBcZP527To60GoD_0mffdjqLiUyWDmmK_F8_FNwG1qfZG37HlcZcCPfv1_41TOUJnuNH7tVXvIQBNePJwsUNaZ9ngreT_8HJE7ye1QZ_fGIhIilqFMAKPjHXA12wAtChtGvOMmihiIaECNqqlpP8qjuHZc39hxugnh5baEh6l2PrgOjpaVpWJPn5Pw-xVN' alt='Photograph of Camilo Castro shown on a placard during a rally with Amnesty International activists and his family in Toulouse to protest his detention, September 20, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Exact disappearance: Family accounts say Castro went missing at the Paraguachon border crossing on June 26, the point that separates Colombia and Venezuela.</li><li>Personal details: Sources identify Castro as a 41-year-old yoga teacher who lived in Colombia and held both French and Chilean nationality.</li><li>Public pressure: Relatives and Amnesty International activists staged demonstrations in France to call for his release, including a rally in Toulouse on September 20, 2025.</li><li>Government role: French authorities said they secured Castro&#x27;s release through diplomatic channels and publicly confirmed his return on November 16, 2025.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>French presidency: President Emmanuel Macron announced Castro&#x27;s release and framed it as a result of French diplomatic efforts to secure his freedom. (<a href='https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20251116-french-national-held-in-venezuela-released-macron'>rfi.fr</a>)</li><li>Family and activists: Castro&#x27;s family said he had crossed the border to renew an expired Colombian residency visa and campaigned with Amnesty International for his release. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/11/16/french-national-held-in-venezuela-released-announces-macron_6747499_4.html'>lemonde.fr</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20251116-french-national-held-in-venezuela-released-macron'>French national held in Venezuela released: Macron</a> - rfi.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/france/20251116-french-chilean-national-held-venezuela-june-released-macron-camilo-castro'>French-Chilean national held in Venezuela since June released, Macron says</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/11/16/french-national-held-in-venezuela-released-announces-macron_6747499_4.html'>French national held in Venezuela released, announces Macron</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/france-secures-release-french-chilean-national-held-venezuela-127567581'>France secures release of French-Chilean national held in Venezuela</a> - abcnews.go.com</li></ul>